CIC/References/ContentTemplates/Text.htm.body:
Text Template
Displays text data. It displays text with highlights, paragraph text or table text.

Note!
See Screen UI example for available display formats of the Text template.


Template field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




bgUrl
URLObject
An object that contains an image URL to display in background
No


highlightText
StringObject or NumberObject
When the object contains text or number to highlight, you can add a digit grouping symbol to the number.
No


imageUrl
URLObject
An object that contains an image URL
No


linkUrl
URLObject
An object that contains a URL which directs a user to a web map when a map image is included
No


mainText
StringObject
An object that contains main text
No


paragraphText
StringObject
An object that contains paragraph text
No


referenceText
StringObject
An object that contains source text information
No


referenceURL
URLObject
An object that contains a source URL
No


sentenceText
StringObject
An object that contains sentence text
No


subText
StringObject
An object that contains sub text
No


tablieList[]
object array
An object array that contains table text. The table has two columns.
No


tablieList[].item1
StringObject
An object that contains text to display in a first column
No


tablieList[].item2
StringObject
An object that contains text to display in a second column
No


tablieList[].item2Link
URLObject or PhoneNumberObject
An object that contains a link URL or phone number of the text in a second column
No


type
string
Content Template delimiter. The value is always "ImageText".
Yes



